release_note: You can now see what notebook your note lives in while browsing tags.
Notejoy for iOS now supports adding all editor styles available on desktop including documents color highlight block quotes code blocks dividers and videos.
Notejoy now offers an auto complete as you type tags in the editor You can now easily rename move or delete notebooks
Bug fixes
Bug fixes.

Easily move bullets lists and tasks up down Create note links by typing Mention everyone in comments Login with Microsoft
Adds the ability to easily clear a search.
Updated app design and improved look on latest iPhones.
This update fixes a crash that would occasionally occur when loading the app.
You can now purchase Notejoy Solo our premium subscription which adds unlimited notebooks personal libraries additional storage password protected notes and so much more.
Added support for emoji in library and notebook names.
Added support for emoji in library and notebook names.
Added support for font colors.
We ve redesigned Notejoy s logo!
This release adds support for import notifications and showing your default notebook on load if you hide the Recent view.
This release includes a few bug fixes including improving the editor in older versions of iOS.
You can now send notes via email. And we ve improved the layout on iPhone 12.
Notejoy now supports dark mode!

This release is packed with new features performance improvements and bug fixes including: You can now take a photo directly from a note Loading the app scrolling through note lists and navigating the sidebar are all now faster than ever We ve brought a ton of our recent desktop releases to mobile including nested notebooks nested tags and hiding sidebar items libraries and tags We fixed a bug that made it difficult to upload an image from your camera roll into a note We improved the cursor position when you tap into edit a note When you click on a Notejoy marketing page link it ll now open in your browser instead of the Notejoy app
Made it easier to share feedback with the Notejoy team.
Adds support for two factor authentication.
Improved support for iPhone XR and iPhone Xs Max devices.
Adds support for password protected notes.
This release brings tags collapsible libraries and archived notebooks and libraries to the iOS app!

We re back with a ton of great updates including: Create team libraries notebooks directly from the app s sidebar Indent un indent bullets lists and checklists with new styling bar actions Access help and share feedback from the sidebar user menu
You can now view uploaded Microsoft Word Excel Powerpoint Google Doc Sheet Slide PDF Audio and Video files right from the iOS app.
Added iPhone X support to make Notejoy look beautiful on the device. Also simplified sign up and added a forgot password option.
